<br>
Best way to prepare for this is to leave /pet attack on a hot key, or even better make a switch target hot key like this:<br>
<br>
Line 1: /pet back off<br>
Line 2: /pet attack (while targeting the troublesome mob of course)<br>
<br>
Root nets, Gooey Goo or Earing of living slime (if I could only be so lucky) offer another route for those emergency situations.<br>
